cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE 

This paper deals with the development of a multilingual named entity transliteration system, which involves natural language processing and machine learning techniques. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with the intersection of computer science and linguistics. The paper also involves the curation of bilingual named entity datasets, which falls under the sub-category cs.IR (Information Retrieval). The evaluation of multiple transliteration methods involves machine learning, which is covered under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper deals with named entities, which is a sub-field of natural language processing and falls under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
